narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I developed a strong understanding of the Spanish language and how to speak it more effectively.
I developed skills that helped me learn Spanish.
I developed a strong understanding of the basics of the Spanish language. I can now engage in comfortable conversation with someone who I am meeting for the first time.

I had a great introduction into the language and culture of Spanish speaking countries. I developed new learning techniques to help me remember vocabulary which I was able to carry her to my other classes and my ability to speak Spanish improved greatly. I really enjoyed taking this class.
This course in particular taught me how to develop a solid foundation to Spanish and Spanish-speaking cultures.
I learned a lot more Spanish than I was expecting to. I developed great study skills.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The class is very well organized to facilitate learning and I can't really think of how one may improve it.

This class is a great way to cover a lot of the basics of Spanish, while also learning about Spanish history and culture. The seminar style was very effective in helping me be immersed in the Spanish language. The professor was also amazing.
Professor Diaz was this courses biggest strength. He was super helpful and always willing to meet with his students.

the classes are interactive and a good pace to allow me to know what's going on and not get lost in the content. The super sites were very relevant and tested my knowledge well however, I don't think that the weekly discussions were of much use.
This course is homework heavy and depends on a high level of studying. However, you do get really detailed feedback on your work which makes learning much easier.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would. It's a great way to learn and advance quickly in Spanish.
Great way to learn a foreign language.
yes, for students that want to start speaking Spanish. it is a good way to start

I would recommend this course to another student. Although it requires a lot of studying through out the semester, the end product is the satisfaction of having a solid grasp of Spanish, enough to understand most basic Spanish in literature, music, podcasts, etc.
